{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"padding"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"edges"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO","text":"Edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO3SetV","text":"Set"},{"kind":"text","text":" = .all, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"length"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV","text":"CGFloat"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"edges","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The set of edges to pad for this view. The default","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set\/all","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"length","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An amount, given in points, to pad this view on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified edges. If you set the value to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", OpenSwiftUI uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a platform-specific default amount. The default value of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parameter is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that’s padded by the specified amount on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified edges.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier to add a specified amount of padding to one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"edges of the view. Indicate the edges to pad by naming either a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value from ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or by specifying an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Swift\/OptionSet","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contains edge values:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text padded by 20 points on the bottom and trailing edges.\")","        .padding([.bottom, .trailing], 20)","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The order in which you apply modifiers matters. The example above","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applies the padding before applying the border to ensure that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"border encompasses the padded region:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can omit either or both of the parameters. If you omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"length","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"OpenSwiftUI uses a default amount of padding. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"omit the ","type":"text"},{"code":"edges","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", OpenSwiftUI applies the padding to all edges. Omit both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to add a default padding all the way around a view. OpenSwiftUI chooses a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default amount of padding that’s appropriate for the platform and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the presentation context.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text with default padding.\")","        .padding()","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above looks like this in iOS under typical conditions:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To control the amount of padding independently for each edge, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-6pgqq"},{"type":"text","text":". To pad all outside edges of a view by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified amount, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/padding(_:)-68shk"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/primitivebuttonstyleconfiguration\/label-swift.struct\/padding(_:_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwi